    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhile debugging #39373 I found this piece of code in `vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua`:\n\n```lua\n      -- Expand the cmdline for a non-error message that doesn't fit.\n      local error_kinds = { rpc_error = 1, emsg = 1, echoerr = 1, lua_error = 1 }\n      if texth.all > ui.cmdheight and (ui.cmdheight == 0 or not error_kinds[kind]) then\n        M.expand_msg(tgt)\n      end\n```\nIt expands any non-error message. Which is probably what most of people would want, but I would love to have some option to avoid expansion at all.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo better illustrate desired behavior I would provide some (pseudo) code that I think should be there:\n\n```lua\n-- Expand the cmdline for a non-error message that doesn't fit.\nlocal error_kinds = { rpc_error = 1, emsg = 1, echoerr = 1, lua_error = 1 }\nlocal not_error = not error_kinds[kind]\nlocal expand = o.cmdexpand -- true by default, set nocmdexpand to no expand\nif texth.all > ui.cmdheight then\n  if expand and not_error then\n    M.expand_msg(tgt)\n  end\nend\n```\n\nIt doesn't seem to add much maintenance burden and is a pretty simple feature (or that's what I think with my little knowledge about the codebase)\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
