            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Do you mean that there should be possibility for messages that have \"cmd\" target to be selectively either expanded or not? I might've missed the point, but shouldn't this behavior be common for all messages routed to \"cmd\"? They are either expanded or not.\n\nIn one of the issues Clason suggested that `:lua print(...)` should not be truncated but is it a final decision? Maybe it's fine to truncate all (or none) with the ability to use `g<` to view the full output. For me I think it would be consistent to press `g<` to view full output, but I might have different usecases than you.",
