            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> They are either expanded or not.\n>\n> ... Clason suggested that `:lua print(...)` should not be truncated but is it a final decision?\n\nWe have [discussed](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38445#issuecomment-4168964233) giving control (aka \"routing\") over how messages are handled based on the message `kind`. Although we haven't thought much about whether this will also control truncation, it's basically the same topic: more control over message behavior.\n\nUpdate: routing by id implemented in:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39734",
